title: Spicer, MSNBC Reporter Lock Horns At Press Briefing — ‘We’re Ending This RIGHT NOW’ [VIDEO]
text:
TOP 5443285 
Sean Spicer and MSNBC’s Kristen Welker entered into a heated exchange during Wednesday’s White House press briefing. Sean Spicer (Getty Images) 
Welker first asked Spicer about a question he skirted earlier in the briefing. 
WATCH: 
“I want to go back to that draft executive that would undo restrictions pertaining to the handling of detainees,” she noted. “Has the President seen that?” “You’re asking me if a document that’s not a White House document he has seen,” Spicer responded. “I don’t believe to the best of my knowledge.” Sean Spicer (Getty Images) “This is the second day in a row that we’re being asked about documents that are not White House documents, and frankly reports that are being published attributing documents to the White House that are not White House documents,” Trump’s press secretary added. “I haven’t attributed,” Welker pushed onward. “Do you know if he’s seen it?” Welker continued to ask Spicer about the document, to which he finally responded, “I’m not going to answer hypotheticals about documents that are floating around.” “OK, Kristen, we’re going to end this right now.”
